fields.title: The Post
fields.description: You've got it made! Get to know your NEW APARTMENT HOME at The Post in Seattle, WA.    The star players may be the city and mountain views, but the homes are a worthy supporting cast. Concrete ceilings, exposed duct work and plank flooring lend an industrial edge. Clean-lined kitchens with plenty of storage and unique pendant lighting are a quiet showpiece. In the one-bedroom apartments, a frosted glass door lets you customize your space.    Where downtown meets Pioneer Square and the waterfront, The Post is on the edge of everything. Sports your game? Walk this way to CenturyLink Stadium and Safeco Field. Chowhound? You'll love the neighborhood grub, from sandwiches at Delicatus to fresh-from-the-oven cinnamon rolls at Grand Central Bakery. From live music at the Owl N' Thistle to European soccer matches at Fado, there's no shortage of nighttime spots to while away an evening. The best part? You can walk to all of it.    Urban, uncompromised.    Waking up in the city has a buzz of its own. Going to bed with a buzz – hey, it happens. (We're looking at you, Owl   Thistle and The Forge Lounge.) On the border of downtown and Pioneer Square, The Post is your portal to an urban experience like no other. You're not like everyone else. Your view shouldn't be either.    Don't Covet the Neighbors Lifestyle. Make it your own!  Ever seen another building in Seattle with a reflecting pool on the roof?  That's what we thought. Take your shoes off, dip your feet in, and stay awhile. On the expansive rooftop, you'll find the sky lounge with demonstration kitchen, theater, game room, library, fitness and yoga rooms. We didn't leave out the dogs, there's a lounge for them too!     Don't miss out on our offer of 1 month free rent!New Luxury Apartments, Stainless Steel Appliances, Luxurious Quartz Countertops, Floor to Ceiling Windows/Hardwood Flooring, Air Conditioning in home, Million Dollar Views w/the best rooftop in Seattle
